name: Bulbasaur
info:
Bulbasaur is a Grass & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Bulbasaur's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 1,115. Bulbasaur evolves into Ivysaur.
					
						"Bulbasaur can be seen napping in bright sunlight. There is a seed on its back. By soaking up the sun's rays, the seed grows progressively larger.

name: Ivysaur
info:
Ivysaur is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Bulbasaur. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Ivysaur's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 1,699. Ivysaur evolves into Venusaur.
					
						"There is a bud on this Pokémon's back. To support its weight, Ivysaur's legs and trunk grow thick and strong. If it starts spending more time lying in the sunlight, it's a sign that the bud will bloom into a large flower soon.

name: Venusaur
info:
Venusaur is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Ivysaur. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Venusaur's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Frenzy Plant and it has a Max CP of 2,720.
					
						"There is a large flower on Venusaur's back. The flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the emotions of people.

name: Charmander
info:
Charmander is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Charmander's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 980. Charmander evolves into Charmeleon.
					
						"The flame that burns at the tip of its tail is an indication of its emotions. The flame wavers when Charmander is enjoying itself. If the Pokémon becomes enraged, the flame burns fiercely.

name: Charmeleon
info:
Charmeleon is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Charmander. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Charmeleon's strongest moveset is Fire Fang & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,653. Charmeleon evolves into Charizard.
					
						"Charmeleon mercilessly destroys its foes using its sharp claws. If it encounters a strong foe, it turns aggressive. In this excited state, the flame at the tip of its tail flares with a bluish white color.

name: Charizard
info:
Charizard is a Fire & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Charmeleon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Electric and Water moves. Charizard's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 2,889.
					
						"Charizard flies around the sky in search of powerful opponents. It breathes fire of such great heat that it melts anything. However, it never turns its fiery breath on any opponent weaker than itself.

name: Squirtle
info:
Squirtle is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Squirtle's strongest moveset is Bubble & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 946. Squirtle evolves into Wartortle.
					
						"Squirtle's shell is not merely used for protection. The shell's rounded shape and the grooves on its surface help minimize resistance in water, enabling this Pokémon to swim at high speeds.

name: Wartortle
info:
Wartortle is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Squirtle. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Wartortle's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 1,488. Wartortle evolves into Blastoise.
					
						"Its tail is large and covered with a rich, thick fur. The tail becomes increasingly deeper in color as Wartortle ages. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this Pokémon's toughness as a battler.

name: Blastoise
info:
Blastoise is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Wartortle. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Blastoise's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,466.
					
						"Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.

name: Caterpie
info:
Caterpie is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Caterpie's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 437. Caterpie evolves into Metapod.
					
						"Caterpie has a voracious appetite. It can devour leaves bigger than its body right before your eyes. From its antenna, this Pokémon releases a terrifically strong odor.

name: Metapod
info:
Metapod is a Bug Pokémon which evolves from Caterpie. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Metapod's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 450. Metapod evolves into Butterfree.
					
						"The shell covering this Pokémon's body is as hard as an iron slab. Metapod does not move very much. It stays still because it is preparing its soft innards for evolution inside the hard shell.

name: Butterfree
info:
Butterfree is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Metapod. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Butterfree's strongest moveset is Confusion & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,827.
					
						"Butterfree has a superior ability to search for delicious honey from flowers. It can even search out, extract, and carry honey from flowers that are blooming over six miles from its nest.

name: Weedle
info:
Weedle is a Bug & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Weedle's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 456. Weedle evolves into Kakuna.
					
						"Weedle has an extremely acute sense of smell. It is capable of distinguishing its favorite kinds of leaves from those it dislikes just by sniffing with its big red proboscis (nose).

name: Kakuna
info:
Kakuna is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Weedle. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Kakuna's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 432. Kakuna evolves into Beedrill.
					
						"Kakuna remains virtually immobile as it clings to a tree. However, on the inside, it is extremely busy as it prepares for its coming evolution. This is evident from how hot the shell becomes to the touch.

name: Beedrill
info:
Beedrill is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Kakuna. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Beedrill's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,846.
					
						"Beedrill is extremely territorial. No one should ever approach its nest—this is for their own safety. If angered, they will attack in a furious swarm.

name: Pidgey
info:
Pidgey is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Pidgey's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 680. Pidgey evolves into Pidgeotto.
					
						"Pidgey has an extremely sharp sense of direction. It is capable of unerringly returning home to its nest, however far it may be removed from its familiar surroundings.

name: Pidgeotto
info:
Pidgeotto is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Pidgey. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Pidgeotto's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 1,194. Pidgeotto evolves into Pidgeot.
					
						"Pidgeotto claims a large area as its own territory. This Pokémon flies around, patrolling its living space. If its territory is violated, it shows no mercy in thoroughly punishing the foe with its sharp claws.

name: Pidgeot
info:
Pidgeot is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Pidgeotto. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Pidgeot's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Hurricane and it has a Max CP of 2,129.
					
						"This Pokémon has a dazzling plumage of beautifully glossy feathers. Many Trainers are captivated by the striking beauty of the feathers on its head, compelling them to choose Pidgeot as their Pokémon.

name: Rattata
info:
Rattata (Alola Form) is a Dark & Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Fairy and Bug moves. Rattata's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Hyper Fang and it has a Max CP of 734. Rattata evolves into Raticate.
					
						"Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly listens by moving its ears around. It is not picky about where it lives—it will make its nest anywhere.

name: Rattata
info:
Rattata (Normal) is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Rattata's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Hyper Fang and it has a Max CP of 734. Rattata evolves into Raticate.
					
						"Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly listens by moving its ears around. It is not picky about where it lives—it will make its nest anywhere.

name: Raticate
info:
Raticate (Alola Form) is a Dark & Normal Pokémon which evolves from Rattata. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Fairy and Bug moves. Raticate's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,705.
					
						"Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.

name: Raticate
info:
Raticate (Normal) is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Rattata. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Raticate's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,730.
					
						"Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.

name: Spearow
info:
Spearow is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Spearow's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 798. Spearow evolves into Fearow.
					
						"Spearow has a very loud cry that can be heard over half a mile away. If its high, keening cry is heard echoing all around, it is a sign that they are warning each other of danger.

name: Fearow
info:
Fearow is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Spearow. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Fearow's strongest moveset is Peck & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 1,997.
					
						"Fearow is recognized by its long neck and elongated beak. They are conveniently shaped for catching prey in soil or water. It deftly moves its long and skinny beak to pluck prey.

name: Ekans
info:
Ekans is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Ekans's strongest moveset is Acid & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 927. Ekans evolves into Arbok.
					
						"Ekans curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any direction with a glare from its upraised head.

name: Arbok
info:
Arbok is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Ekans. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Arbok's strongest moveset is Acid & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 1,921.
					
						"This Pokémon is terrifically strong in order to constrict things with its body. It can even flatten steel oil drums. Once Arbok wraps its body around its foe, escaping its crushing embrace is impossible.

name: Pikachu
info:
Pikachu is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Pichu. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Pikachu's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 938. Pikachu evolves into Raichu.
					
						"Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokémon mistook the intensity of its charge.

name: Raichu
info:
Raichu (Normal) is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Pikachu. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Raichu's strongest moveset is Spark & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 2,182.
					
						"If the electrical sacs become excessively charged, Raichu plants its tail in the ground and discharges. Scorched patches of ground will be found near this Pokémon's nest.

name: Raichu
info:
Raichu (Alola Form) is an Electric & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Pikachu. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Bug and Ghost moves. Raichu's strongest moveset is Spark & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 2,286.
					
						"If the electrical sacs become excessively charged, Raichu plants its tail in the ground and discharges. Scorched patches of ground will be found near this Pokémon's nest.

name: Sandshrew
info:
Sandshrew (Alola Form) is an Ice & Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting and Ground moves. Sandshrew's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 1,293. Sandshrew evolves into Sandslash.
					
						"Sandshrew's body is configured to absorb water without waste, enabling it to survive in an arid desert. This Pokémon curls up to protect itself from its enemies.

name: Sandshrew
info:
Sandshrew (Normal) is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Sandshrew's strongest moveset is Mud Shot & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,261. Sandshrew evolves into Sandslash.
					
						"Sandshrew's body is configured to absorb water without waste, enabling it to survive in an arid desert. This Pokémon curls up to protect itself from its enemies.

name: Sandslash
info:
Sandslash (Normal) is a Ground Pokémon which evolves from Sandshrew. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Sandslash's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,374.
					
						"Sandslash's body is covered by tough spikes, which are hardened sections of its hide. Once a year, the old spikes fall out, to be replaced with new spikes that grow out from beneath the old ones.

name: Sandslash
info:
Sandslash (Alola Form) is an Ice & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Sandshrew. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting and Ground moves. Sandslash's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 2,432.
					
						"Sandslash's body is covered by tough spikes, which are hardened sections of its hide. Once a year, the old spikes fall out, to be replaced with new spikes that grow out from beneath the old ones.

name: Nidoran♀
info:
Nidoran♀ is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Nidoran♀'s strongest moveset is Poison Sting & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 816. Nidoran♀ evolves into Nidorina.
					
						"Nidoran♀ has barbs that secrete a powerful poison. They are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied Pokémon. When enraged, it releases a horrible toxin from its horn.

name: Nidorina
info:
Nidorina is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Nidoran♀. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Nidorina's strongest moveset is Poison Sting & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,309. Nidorina evolves into Nidoqueen.
					
						"When Nidorina are with their friends or family, they keep their barbs tucked away to prevent hurting each other. This Pokémon appears to become nervous if separated from the others.

name: Nidoqueen
info:
Nidoqueen is a Poison & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Nidorina. It is vulnerable to Water, Ground, Ice and Psychic moves. Nidoqueen's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Earth Power and it has a Max CP of 2,488.
					
						"Nidoqueen's body is encased in extremely hard scales. It is adept at sending foes flying with harsh tackles. This Pokémon is at its strongest when it is defending its young.

name: Nidoran♂
info:
Nidoran♂ is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Nidoran♂'s strongest moveset is Poison Sting & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 860. Nidoran♂ evolves into Nidorino.
					
						"Nidoran♂ has developed muscles for moving its ears. Thanks to them, the ears can be freely moved in any direction. Even the slightest sound does not escape this Pokémon's notice.

name: Nidorino
info:
Nidorino is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Nidoran♂. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Nidorino's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,393. Nidorino evolves into Nidoking.
					
						"Nidorino has a horn that is harder than a diamond. If it senses a hostile presence, all the barbs on its back bristle up at once, and it challenges the foe with all its might.

name: Nidoking
info:
Nidoking is a Poison & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Nidorino. It is vulnerable to Water, Ground, Ice and Psychic moves. Nidoking's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Earth Power and it has a Max CP of 2,567.
					
						"Nidoking's thick tail packs enormously destructive power. With one swing, it can topple a metal transmission tower. Once this Pokémon goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.

name: Clefairy
info:
Clefairy is a Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Cleffa. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Clefairy's strongest moveset is Pound & Moonblast and it has a Max CP of 1,155. Clefairy evolves into Clefable.
					
						"On every night of a full moon, groups of this Pokémon come out to play. When dawn arrives, the tired Clefairy return to their quiet mountain retreats and go to sleep nestled up against each other.

name: Clefable
info:
Clefable is a Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Clefairy. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Clefable's strongest moveset is Charm Fast & Meteor Mash and it has a Max CP of 2,437.
					
						"Clefable moves by skipping lightly as if it were flying using its wings. Its bouncy step lets it even walk on water. It is known to take strolls on lakes on quiet, moonlit nights.

name: Vulpix
info:
Vulpix (Alola Form) is an Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Vulpix's strongest moveset is Powder Snow & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 883. Vulpix evolves into Ninetales.
					
						"At the time of its birth, Vulpix has one white tail. The tail separates into six if this Pokémon receives plenty of love from its Trainer. The six tails become magnificently curled.

name: Vulpix
info:
Vulpix (Normal) is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Vulpix's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 883. Vulpix evolves into Ninetales.
					
						"At the time of its birth, Vulpix has one white tail. The tail separates into six if this Pokémon receives plenty of love from its Trainer. The six tails become magnificently curled.

name: Ninetales
info:
Ninetales (Normal) is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Vulpix. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Ninetales's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 2,279.
					
						"Ninetales casts a sinister light from its bright red eyes to gain total control over its foe's mind. This Pokémon is said to live for a thousand years.

name: Ninetales
info:
Ninetales (Alola Form) is an Ice & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Vulpix. It is vulnerable to Steel, Fire, Poison and Rock moves. Ninetales's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 2,309.
					
						"Ninetales casts a sinister light from its bright red eyes to gain total control over its foe's mind. This Pokémon is said to live for a thousand years.

name: Jigglypuff
info:
Jigglypuff is a Normal & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Igglybuff. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Jigglypuff's strongest moveset is Pound & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 724. Jigglypuff evolves into Wigglytuff.
					
						"Jigglypuff's vocal cords can freely adjust the wavelength of its voice. This Pokémon uses this ability to sing at precisely the right wavelength to make its foes most drowsy.

name: Wigglytuff
info:
Wigglytuff is a Normal & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Jigglypuff. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Wigglytuff's strongest moveset is Pound & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,926.
					
						"Wigglytuff has large, saucerlike eyes. The surfaces of its eyes are always covered with a thin layer of tears. If any dust gets in this Pokémon's eyes, it is quickly washed away.

name: Zubat
info:
Zubat is a Poison & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Psychic and Electric moves. Zubat's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Air Cutter and it has a Max CP of 667. Zubat evolves into Golbat.
					
						"Zubat remains quietly unmoving in a dark spot during the bright daylight hours. It does so because prolonged exposure to the sun causes its body to become slightly burned.

name: Golbat
info:
Golbat is a Poison & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Zubat. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Psychic and Electric moves. Golbat's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,976. Golbat evolves into Crobat.
					
						"Golbat loves to drink the blood of living things. It is particularly active in the pitch black of night. This Pokémon flits around in the night skies, seeking fresh blood.

name: Oddish
info:
Oddish is a Grass & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Oddish's strongest moveset is Acid & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,228. Oddish evolves into Gloom.
					
						"During the daytime, Oddish buries itself in soil to absorb nutrients from the ground using its entire body. The more fertile the soil, the glossier its leaves become.

name: Gloom
info:
Gloom is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Oddish. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Gloom's strongest moveset is Acid & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,681. Gloom evolves into Vileplume, Bellossom.
					
						"Gloom releases a foul fragrance from the pistil of its flower. When faced with danger, the stench worsens. If this Pokémon is feeling calm and secure, it does not release its usual stinky aroma.

name: Vileplume
info:
Vileplume is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Gloom. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Vileplume's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,559.
					
						"Vileplume's toxic pollen triggers atrocious allergy attacks. That's why it is advisable never to approach any attractive flowers in a jungle, however pretty they may be.

name: Paras
info:
Paras is a Bug & Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Rock, Bug and Ice moves. Paras's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Seed Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,018. Paras evolves into Parasect.
					
						"Night after night, they sneak into people's homes seeking food. A massive outbreak of them has become an issue of public concern.

name: Parasect
info:
Parasect is a Bug & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Paras. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Rock, Bug and Ice moves. Parasect's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,859.
					
						"Parasect is known to infest large trees en masse and drain nutrients from the lower trunk and roots. When an infested tree dies, they move onto another tree all at once.

name: Venonat
info:
Venonat is a Bug & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Venonat's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Signal Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,004. Venonat evolves into Venomoth.
					
						"It commands a nest of Rattata. Different nests don't get along, whipping up severe fights over feeding grounds.

name: Venomoth
info:
Venomoth is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Venonat. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Venomoth's strongest moveset is Infestation & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 2,082.
					
						"Venomoth is nocturnal—it is a Pokémon that only becomes active at night. Its favorite prey are small insects that gather around streetlights, attracted by the light in the darkness.

name: Diglett
info:
Diglett (Normal) is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Diglett's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Mud Bomb and it has a Max CP of 676. Diglett evolves into Dugtrio.
					
						"When you rub its cheeks, a sweet fragrance comes wafting out. However, you'll also get a light shock!

name: Diglett
info:
Diglett (Alola Form) is a Ground & Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Water, Ground and Fighting moves. Diglett's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Mud Bomb and it has a Max CP of 681. Diglett evolves into Dugtrio.
					
						"When you rub its cheeks, a sweet fragrance comes wafting out. However, you'll also get a light shock!

name: Dugtrio
info:
Dugtrio (Normal) is a Ground Pokémon which evolves from Diglett. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Dugtrio's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 1,567.
					
						"Dugtrio are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly.

name: Dugtrio
info:
Dugtrio (Alola Form) is a Ground & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Diglett. It is vulnerable to Fire, Water, Ground and Fighting moves. Dugtrio's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 1,897.
					
						"Dugtrio are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly.

name: Meowth
info:
Meowth (Alola Form) is a Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Meowth's strongest moveset is Bite & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 797. Meowth evolves into Persian.
					
						"The skin on its back is as hard as steel. Predators go after its soft belly, so it clings to the ground desperately.

name: Meowth
info:
Meowth (Normal) is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Meowth's strongest moveset is Scratch & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 748. Meowth evolves into Persian.
					
						"The skin on its back is as hard as steel. Predators go after its soft belly, so it clings to the ground desperately.

name: Persian
info:
Persian (Alola Form) is a Dark Pokémon which evolves from Meowth. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Persian's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 1,771.
					
						"Persian has six bold whiskers that give it a look of toughness. The whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in the Pokémon's surrounding vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.

name: Persian
info:
Persian (Normal) is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Meowth. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Persian's strongest moveset is Scratch & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,689.
					
						"Persian has six bold whiskers that give it a look of toughness. The whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in the Pokémon's surrounding vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.

name: Psyduck
info:
Psyduck is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Psyduck's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 1,106. Psyduck evolves into Golduck.
					
						"A long, long time ago, it lived in the desert. With its sharp claws fully extended, it can climb right up an iceberg without slipping.

name: Golduck
info:
Golduck is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Psyduck. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Golduck's strongest moveset is Confusion & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,450.
					
						"The webbed flippers on its forelegs and hind legs and the streamlined body of Golduck give it frightening speed. This Pokémon is definitely much faster than even the most athletic swimmer.

name: Mankey
info:
Mankey is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Mankey's strongest moveset is Karate Chop & Cross Chop and it has a Max CP of 1,164. Mankey evolves into Primeape.
					
						"They live together in a skulk, helping one another. Before eating their prey, they freeze it solid with their –58 degree Fahrenheit breath.

name: Primeape
info:
Primeape is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Mankey. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Primeape's strongest moveset is Counter & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,288.
					
						"When Primeape becomes furious, its blood circulation is boosted. In turn, its muscles are made even stronger. However, it also becomes much less intelligent at the same time.

name: Growlithe
info:
Growlithe is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Growlithe's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,243. Growlithe evolves into Arcanine.
					
						"Some said that deities visited mountains where Ninetales live, so in times long past, no one was allowed to go into those mountains.

name: Arcanine
info:
Arcanine is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Growlithe. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Arcanine's strongest moveset is Fire Fang & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 3,029.
					
						"Arcanine is known for its high speed. It is said to be capable of running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within this Pokémon's body is its source of power.

name: Poliwag
info:
Poliwag is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Poliwag's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 829. Poliwag evolves into Poliwhirl.
					
						"The need to dig through volcanic rock in the ground has made them more powerful than the Diglett of other regions.

name: Poliwhirl
info:
Poliwhirl is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Poliwag. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Poliwhirl's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,419. Poliwhirl evolves into Poliwrath, Politoed.
					
						"The surface of Poliwhirl's body is always wet and slick with a slimy fluid. Because of this slippery covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.

name: Poliwrath
info:
Poliwrath is a Water & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Poliwhirl. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying, Psychic, Electric and Grass moves. Poliwrath's strongest moveset is Bubble & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 2,586.
					
						"Its shining gold whiskers are advanced sensors that can detect vibrations from sounds several miles away.

name: Abra
info:
Abra is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Abra's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,342. Abra evolves into Kadabra.
					
						"Abra sleeps for 18 hours a day. However, it can sense the presence of foes even while it is sleeping. In such a situation, this Pokémon immediately teleports to safety.

name: Kadabra
info:
Kadabra is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Abra. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Kadabra's strongest moveset is Confusion & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,059. Kadabra evolves into Alakazam.
					
						"A royal house that flourished in the distant past brought it here from another region. Meowth is both selfish and prideful.

name: Alakazam
info:
Alakazam is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Kadabra. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Alakazam's strongest moveset is Confusion & Future Sight and it has a Max CP of 3,057.
					
						"Alakazam's brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This Pokémon holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.

name: Machop
info:
Machop is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Machop's strongest moveset is Karate Chop & Cross Chop and it has a Max CP of 1,278. Machop evolves into Machoke.
					
						"Its round face is a symbol of wealth. Persian that have bigger, plumper faces are considered more beautiful.

name: Machoke
info:
Machoke is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Machop. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Machoke's strongest moveset is Karate Chop & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 2,031. Machoke evolves into Machamp.
					
						"Machoke's thoroughly toned muscles possess the hardness of steel. This Pokémon has so much strength, it can easily hold aloft a sumo wrestler on just one finger.

name: Machamp
info:
Machamp is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Machoke. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Machamp's strongest moveset is Counter & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 3,056.
					
						"Geodude compete against each other with headbutts. The iron sand on their heads will stick to whichever one has stronger magnetism.

name: Bellsprout
info:
Bellsprout is a Grass & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Bellsprout's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 1,033. Bellsprout evolves into Weepinbell.
					
						"Bellsprout's thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack, however strong it may be. From its mouth, this Pokémon spits a corrosive fluid that melts even iron.

name: Weepinbell
info:
Weepinbell is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Bellsprout. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Weepinbell's strongest moveset is Acid & Power Whip and it has a Max CP of 1,611. Weepinbell evolves into Victreebel.
					
						"Graveler's entire body is tinged with electricity due to the stones it likes to eat. It's very quick-tempered.

name: Victreebel
info:
Victreebel is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Weepinbell. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Victreebel's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,431.
					
						"Victreebel has a long vine that extends from its head. This vine is waved and flicked about as if it were an animal to attract prey. When an unsuspecting prey draws near, this Pokémon swallows it whole.

name: Tentacool
info:
Tentacool is a Water & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Psychic and Electric moves. Tentacool's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,040. Tentacool evolves into Tentacruel.
					
						"It shoots large rocks that are charged with electricity. Tremendous electric shocks are flung out across the whole area of impact.

name: Tentacruel
info:
Tentacruel is a Water & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Tentacool. It is vulnerable to Ground, Psychic and Electric moves. Tentacruel's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,422.
					
						"Tentacruel has large red orbs on its head. The orbs glow before lashing the vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast. This Pokémon's outburst creates rough waves around it.

name: Geodude
info:
Geodude (Normal) is a Rock & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Geodude's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 1,293. Geodude evolves into Graveler.
					
						"Brought to Alola to solve the garbage problem, Grimer seems to relish any and all kinds of trash.

name: Geodude
info:
Geodude (Alola Form) is a Rock & Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Geodude's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,293. Geodude evolves into Graveler.
					
						"Brought to Alola to solve the garbage problem, Grimer seems to relish any and all kinds of trash.

name: Graveler
info:
Graveler (Normal) is a Rock & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Geodude. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Graveler's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 1,897. Graveler evolves into Golem.
					
						"Graveler grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This Pokémon eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis.

name: Graveler
info:
Graveler (Alola Form) is a Rock & Electric Pokémon which evolves from Geodude. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Graveler's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,897. Graveler evolves into Golem.
					
						"Graveler grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This Pokémon eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis.

name: Golem
info:
Golem (Alola Form) is a Rock & Electric Pokémon which evolves from Graveler. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Golem's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 2,949.
					
						"What look like fangs and claws are actually crystallized poison that will afflict you at a mere touch, so don't get too close.

name: Golem
info:
Golem (Normal) is a Rock & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Graveler. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Golem's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 2,949.
					
						"What look like fangs and claws are actually crystallized poison that will afflict you at a mere touch, so don't get too close.

name: Ponyta
info:
Ponyta is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Ponyta's strongest moveset is Ember & Flame Charge and it has a Max CP of 1,697. Ponyta evolves into Rapidash.
					
						"Ponyta is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. This Pokémon becomes stronger by stumbling and falling to keep up with its parent.

name: Rapidash
info:
Rapidash is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Ponyta. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Rapidash's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 2,461.
					
						"It swings its long neck like a whip and smacks its opponents. This makes Exeggutor itself dizzy, too.

name: Slowpoke
info:
Slowpoke is a Water & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ghost, Dark, Electric, Grass and Bug moves. Slowpoke's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psyshock and it has a Max CP of 1,226. Slowpoke evolves into Slowbro, Slowking.
					
						"Slowpoke uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in water at the side of a river. However, this Pokémon often forgets what it's doing and often spends entire days just loafing at water's edge.

name: Slowbro
info:
Slowbro is a Water & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Slowpoke. It is vulnerable to Ghost, Dark, Electric, Grass and Bug moves. Slowbro's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,545.
					
						"When it beats opponents with its bone, the cursed flames spread to them. No amount of water will stop those flames from burning.

name: Magnemite
info:
Magnemite is an Electric & Steel Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fire and Fighting moves. Magnemite's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,362. Magnemite evolves into Magneton.
					
						"Magnemite attaches itself to power lines to feed on electricity. If your house has a power outage, check your circuit breakers. You may find a large number of this Pokémon clinging to the breaker box.

name: Magneton
info:
Magneton is an Electric & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Magnemite. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fire and Fighting moves. Magneton's strongest moveset is Spark & Zap Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,485. Magneton evolves into Magnezone.
					
						"Magneton emits a powerful magnetic force that is fatal to mechanical devices. As a result, large cities sound sirens to warn citizens of large-scale outbreaks of this Pokémon.

name: Farfetch'd
info:
Farfetch'd is a regional Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Farfetch'd's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Leaf Blade and it has a Max CP of 1,236. This Pokémon is only found in Asia.
					
						"Farfetch'd is always seen with a stalk from a plant of some sort. Apparently, there are good stalks and bad stalks. This Pokémon has been known to fight with others over stalks.

name: Doduo
info:
Doduo is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Doduo's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Drill Peck and it has a Max CP of 1,200. Doduo evolves into Dodrio.
					
						"Doduo's two heads never sleep at the same time. Its two heads take turns sleeping, so one head can always keep watch for enemies while the other one sleeps.

name: Dodrio
info:
Dodrio is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Doduo. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Dodrio's strongest moveset is Steel Wing & Drill Peck and it has a Max CP of 2,362.
					
						"Watch out if Dodrio's three heads are looking in three separate directions. It's a sure sign that it is on its guard. Don't go near this Pokémon if it's being wary—it may decide to peck you.

name: Seel
info:
Seel is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Seel's strongest moveset is Lick & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 971. Seel evolves into Dewgong.
					
						"Seel hunts for prey in the frigid sea underneath sheets of ice. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.

name: Dewgong
info:
Dewgong is a Water & Ice Pokémon which evolves from Seel. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Dewgong's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 1,985.
					
						"Dewgong loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this Pokémon sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.

name: Grimer
info:
Grimer (Alola Form) is a Poison & Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Grimer's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,374. Grimer evolves into Muk.
					
						"Grimer's sludgy and rubbery body can be forced through any opening, however small it may be. This Pokémon enters sewer pipes to drink filthy wastewater.

name: Grimer
info:
Grimer (Normal) is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Grimer's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,374. Grimer evolves into Muk.
					
						"Grimer's sludgy and rubbery body can be forced through any opening, however small it may be. This Pokémon enters sewer pipes to drink filthy wastewater.

name: Muk
info:
Muk (Alola Form) is a Poison & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Grimer. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Muk's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 2,757.
					
						"From Muk's body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this Pokémon's body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.

name: Muk
info:
Muk (Normal) is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Grimer. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Muk's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 2,757.
					
						"From Muk's body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this Pokémon's body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.

name: Shellder
info:
Shellder is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Shellder's strongest moveset is Tackle & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,080. Shellder evolves into Cloyster.
					
						"At night, this Pokémon uses its broad tongue to burrow a hole in the seafloor sand and then sleep in it. While it is sleeping, Shellder closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.

name: Cloyster
info:
Cloyster is a Water & Ice Pokémon which evolves from Shellder. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Cloyster's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,547.
					
						"Cloyster is capable of swimming in the sea. It does so by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. This Pokémon shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.

name: Gastly
info:
Gastly is a Ghost & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Ghost and Psychic moves. Gastly's strongest moveset is Lick & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,229. Gastly evolves into Haunter.
					
						"Gastly is largely composed of gaseous matter. When exposed to a strong wind, the gaseous body quickly dwindles away. Groups of this Pokémon cluster under the eaves of houses to escape the ravages of wind.

name: Haunter
info:
Haunter is a Ghost & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Gastly. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Ghost and Psychic moves. Haunter's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,963. Haunter evolves into Gengar.
					
						"Haunter is a dangerous Pokémon. If one beckons you while floating in darkness, you must never approach it. This Pokémon will try to lick you with its tongue and steal your life away.

name: Gengar
info:
Gengar is a Ghost & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Haunter. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Ghost and Psychic moves. Gengar's strongest moveset is Lick & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,878.
					
						"Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a Gengar running past you, pretending to be your shadow.

name: Onix
info:
Onix is a Rock & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Onix's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 1,101. Onix evolves into Steelix.
					
						"Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.

name: Drowzee
info:
Drowzee is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Drowzee's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psyshock and it has a Max CP of 1,040. Drowzee evolves into Hypno.
					
						"If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that one of these Pokémon is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.

name: Hypno
info:
Hypno is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Drowzee. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Hypno's strongest moveset is Confusion & Future Sight and it has a Max CP of 2,090.
					
						"Hypno holds a pendulum in its hand. The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum lull the foe into a deep state of hypnosis. While this Pokémon searches for prey, it polishes the pendulum.

name: Krabby
info:
Krabby is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Krabby's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,561. Krabby evolves into Kingler.
					
						"Krabby live on beaches, burrowed inside holes dug into the sand. On sandy beaches with little in the way of food, these Pokémon can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.

name: Kingler
info:
Kingler is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Krabby. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Kingler's strongest moveset is Bubble & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 2,829.
					
						"Kingler has an enormous, oversized claw. It waves this huge claw in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, the Pokémon quickly tires.

name: Voltorb
info:
Voltorb is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Voltorb's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,010. Voltorb evolves into Electrode.
					
						"Voltorb was first sighted at a company that manufactures Poké Balls. The link between that sighting and the fact that this Pokémon looks very similar to a Poké Ball remains a mystery.

name: Electrode
info:
Electrode is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Voltorb. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Electrode's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 2,099.
					
						"Electrode eats electricity in the atmosphere. On days when lightning strikes, you can see this Pokémon exploding all over the place from eating too much electricity.

name: Exeggcute
info:
Exeggcute is a Grass & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fire, Ice, Flying, Poison, Dark and Ghost moves. Exeggcute's strongest moveset is Confusion & Seed Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,175. Exeggcute evolves into Exeggutor.
					
						"This Pokémon consists of six eggs that form a closely knit cluster. The six eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear on the eggs, Exeggcute is close to evolution.

name: Exeggutor
info:
Exeggutor (Alola Form) is a Grass & Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Exeggcute. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy, Flying, Poison, Dragon and Bug moves. Exeggutor's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,014.
					
						"Exeggutor originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form Exeggcute.

name: Exeggutor
info:
Exeggutor (Normal) is a Grass & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Exeggcute. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fire, Ice, Flying, Poison, Dark and Ghost moves. Exeggutor's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,014.
					
						"Exeggutor originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form Exeggcute.

name: Cubone
info:
Cubone is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Cubone's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,019. Cubone evolves into Marowak.
					
						"Cubone pines for the mother it will never see again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in the full moon, it cries. The stains on the skull the Pokémon wears are made by the tears it sheds.

name: Marowak
info:
Marowak (Alola Form) is a Fire & Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Cubone. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Rock, Ghost and Water moves. Marowak's strongest moveset is Hex & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,835.
					
						"Marowak is the evolved form of a Cubone that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This Pokémon's tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.

name: Marowak
info:
Marowak (Normal) is a Ground Pokémon which evolves from Cubone. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Marowak's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 1,835.
					
						"Marowak is the evolved form of a Cubone that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This Pokémon's tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.

name: Hitmonlee
info:
Hitmonlee is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Tyrogue. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Hitmonlee's strongest moveset is Low Kick & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,576.
					
						"Hitmonlee's legs freely contract and stretch. Using these springlike legs, it bowls over foes with devastating kicks. After battle, it rubs down its legs and loosens the muscles to overcome fatigue.

name: Hitmonchan
info:
Hitmonchan is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Tyrogue. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Hitmonchan's strongest moveset is Counter & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,332.
					
						"Hitmonchan is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who had been working toward a world championship. This Pokémon has an indomitable spirit and will never give up in the face of adversity.

name: Lickitung
info:
Lickitung is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Lickitung's strongest moveset is Lick & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,411. Lickitung evolves into Lickilicky.
					
						"Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.

name: Koffing
info:
Koffing is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Koffing's strongest moveset is Infestation & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,214. Koffing evolves into Weezing.
					
						"If Koffing becomes agitated, it raises the toxicity of its internal gases and jets them out from all over its body. This Pokémon may also overinflate its round body, then explode.

name: Weezing
info:
Weezing is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Koffing. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Weezing's strongest moveset is Infestation & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 2,293.
					
						"Weezing loves the gases given off by rotted kitchen garbage. This Pokémon will find a dirty, unkempt house and make it its home. At night, when the people in the house are asleep, it will go through the trash.

name: Rhyhorn
info:
Rhyhorn is a Ground & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Rhyhorn's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Bulldoze and it has a Max CP of 1,651. Rhyhorn evolves into Rhydon.
					
						"Rhyhorn runs in a straight line, smashing everything in its path. It is not bothered even if it rushes headlong into a block of steel. This Pokémon may feel some pain from the collision the next day, however.

name: Rhydon
info:
Rhydon is a Ground & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Rhyhorn. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Rhydon's strongest moveset is Mud-Slap & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 3,179. Rhydon evolves into Rhyperior.
					
						"Rhydon's horn can crush even uncut diamonds. One sweeping blow of its tail can topple a building. This Pokémon's hide is extremely tough. Even direct cannon hits don't leave a scratch.

name: Chansey
info:
Chansey is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Happiny. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Chansey's strongest moveset is Pound & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,255. Chansey evolves into Blissey.
					
						"Chansey lays nutritionally excellent eggs on an everyday basis. The eggs are so delicious, they are easily and eagerly devoured by even those people who have lost their appetite.

name: Tangela
info:
Tangela is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Tangela's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 2,238. Tangela evolves into Tangrowth.
					
						"Tangela's vines snap off easily if they are grabbed. This happens without pain, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by newly grown vines the very next day.

name: Kangaskhan
info:
Kangaskhan is a regional Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Kangaskhan's strongest moveset is Low Kick & Outrage and it has a Max CP of 2,586. This Pokémon is only found in Australasia.
					
						"If you come across a young Kangaskhan playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby Pokémon's parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.

name: Horsea
info:
Horsea is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Horsea's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,056. Horsea evolves into Seadra.
					
						"Horsea eats small insects and moss off of rocks. If the ocean current turns fast, this Pokémon anchors itself by wrapping its tail around rocks or coral to prevent being washed away.

name: Seadra
info:
Seadra is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Horsea. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Seadra's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,093. Seadra evolves into Kingdra.
					
						"Seadra sleeps after wriggling itself between the branches of coral. Those trying to harvest coral are occasionally stung by this Pokémon's poison barbs if they fail to notice it.

name: Goldeen
info:
Goldeen is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Goldeen's strongest moveset is Peck & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 1,152. Goldeen evolves into Seaking.
					
						"Goldeen is a very beautiful Pokémon with fins that billow elegantly in water. However, don't let your guard down around this Pokémon—it could ram you powerfully with its horn.

name: Seaking
info:
Seaking is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Goldeen. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Seaking's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,162.
					
						"In the autumn, Seaking males can be seen performing courtship dances in riverbeds to woo females. During this season, this Pokémon's body coloration is at its most beautiful.

name: Staryu
info:
Staryu is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Staryu's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,157. Staryu evolves into Starmie.
					
						"Staryu's center section has an organ called the core that shines bright red. If you go to a beach toward the end of summer, the glowing cores of these Pokémon look like the stars in the sky.

name: Starmie
info:
Starmie is a Water & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Staryu. It is vulnerable to Ghost, Dark, Electric, Grass and Bug moves. Starmie's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,584.
					
						"Starmie's center section—the core—glows brightly in seven colors. Because of its luminous nature, this Pokémon has been given the nickname “the gem of the sea.”

name: Mr. Mime
info:
Mr. Mime is a regional Psychic & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Mime Jr.. It is vulnerable to Poison, Ghost and Steel moves. Mr. Mime's strongest moveset is Confusion & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,228. This Pokémon is only found in Europe.
					
						"Mr. Mime is a master of pantomime. Its gestures and motions convince watchers that something unseeable actually exists. Once the watchers are convinced, the unseeable thing exists as if it were real.

name: Scyther
info:
Scyther is a Bug & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Scyther's strongest moveset is Air Slash & X-Scissor and it has a Max CP of 2,706. Scyther evolves into Scizor.
					
						"Scyther is blindingly fast. Its blazing speed enhances the effectiveness of the twin scythes on its forearms. This Pokémon's scythes are so effective, they can slice through thick logs in one wicked stroke.

name: Jynx
info:
Jynx is an Ice & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Smoochum. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Rock, Bug, Ghost and Steel moves. Jynx's strongest moveset is Confusion & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,555.
					
						"Jynx walks rhythmically, swaying and shaking its hips as if it were dancing. Its motions are so bouncingly alluring, people seeing it are compelled to shake their hips without giving any thought to what they are doing.

name: Electabuzz
info:
Electabuzz is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Elekid. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Electabuzz's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 2,334. Electabuzz evolves into Electivire.
					
						"When a storm arrives, gangs of this Pokémon compete with each other to scale heights that are likely to be stricken by lightning bolts. Some towns use Electabuzz in place of lightning rods.

name: Magmar
info:
Magmar is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Magby. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Magmar's strongest moveset is Ember & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 2,394. Magmar evolves into Magmortar.
					
						"In battle, Magmar blows out intensely hot flames from all over its body to intimidate its opponent. This Pokémon's fiery bursts create heat waves that ignite grass and trees in its surroundings.

name: Pinsir
info:
Pinsir is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Pinsir's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & X-Scissor and it has a Max CP of 2,959.
					
						"Pinsir is astoundingly strong. It can grip a foe weighing twice its weight in its horns and easily lift it. This Pokémon's movements turn sluggish in cold places.

name: Tauros
info:
Tauros is a regional Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Tauros's strongest moveset is Tackle & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 2,620. This Pokémon is only found in North America.
					
						"This Pokémon is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for Tauros to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.

name: Magikarp
info:
Magikarp is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Magikarp's strongest moveset is Splash & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 274. Magikarp evolves into Gyarados.
					
						"Magikarp is a pathetic excuse for a Pokémon that is only capable of flopping and splashing. This behavior prompted scientists to undertake research into it.

name: Gyarados
info:
Gyarados is a Water & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Magikarp. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Gyarados's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 3,391.
					
						"When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon's wildly violent nature.

name: Lapras
info:
Lapras is a Water & Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Lapras's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Surf and it has a Max CP of 2,641.
					
						"People have driven Lapras almost to the point of extinction. In the evenings, this Pokémon is said to sing plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind still remain.

name: Ditto
info:
Ditto is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Ditto's strongest moveset is Transform & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 832.
					
						"Ditto rearranges its cell structure to transform itself into other shapes. However, if it tries to transform itself into something by relying on its memory, this Pokémon manages to get details wrong.

name: Eevee
info:
Eevee is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Eevee's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Last Resort and it has a Max CP of 1,071. Eevee evolves into Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon.
					
						"Eevee has an unstable genetic makeup that suddenly mutates due to the environment in which it lives. Radiation from various stones causes this Pokémon to evolve.

name: Vaporeon
info:
Vaporeon is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Vaporeon's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 3,114.
					
						"Vaporeon underwent a spontaneous mutation and grew fins and gills that allow it to live underwater. This Pokémon has the ability to freely control water.

name: Jolteon
info:
Jolteon is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Jolteon's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 2,888.
					
						"Jolteon's cells generate a low level of electricity. This power is amplified by the static electricity of its fur, enabling the Pokémon to drop thunderbolts. The bristling fur is made of electrically charged needles.

name: Flareon
info:
Flareon is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Flareon's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 3,029.
					
						"Flareon's fluffy fur has a functional purpose—it releases heat into the air so that its body does not get excessively hot. This Pokémon's body temperature can rise to a maximum of 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
info:
Porygon is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Porygon's strongest moveset is Hidden Power & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,720. Porygon evolves into Porygon2.
					
						"Porygon is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data and entering cyberspace. This Pokémon is copy protected so it cannot be duplicated by copying.

name: Omanyte
info:
Omanyte is a Rock & Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Omanyte's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Rock Blast and it has a Max CP of 1,544. Omanyte evolves into Omastar.
					
						"Omanyte is one of the ancient and long-since-extinct Pokémon that have been regenerated from fossils by people. If attacked by an enemy, it withdraws itself inside its hard shell.

name: Omastar
info:
Omastar is a Rock & Water Pokémon which evolves from Omanyte. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Omastar's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,786.
					
						"Omastar uses its tentacles to capture its prey. It is believed to have become extinct because its shell grew too large and heavy, causing its movements to become too slow and ponderous.

name: Kabuto
info:
Kabuto is a Rock & Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Kabuto's strongest moveset is Scratch & Ancient Power and it has a Max CP of 1,370. Kabuto evolves into Kabutops.
					
						"Kabuto is a Pokémon that has been regenerated from a fossil. However, in extremely rare cases, living examples have been discovered. The Pokémon has not changed at all for 300 million years.

name: Kabutops
info:
Kabutops is a Rock & Water Pokémon which evolves from Kabuto. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Kabutops's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 2,713.
					
						"Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.

name: Aerodactyl
info:
Aerodactyl is a Rock & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Steel, Water and Electric moves. Aerodactyl's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 2,783.
					
						"Aerodactyl is a Pokémon from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from genetic material extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies in ancient times.

name: Snorlax
info:
Snorlax is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Munchlax. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Snorlax's strongest moveset is Lick & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,225.
					
						"Snorlax's typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile Pokémon that there are children who use its expansive belly as a place to play.

name: Articuno
info:
Articuno is a legendary Ice & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Electric and Steel moves. Articuno's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,051.
					
						"Articuno is a Legendary Pokémon that can control ice. The flapping of its wings chills the air. As a result, it is said that when this Pokémon flies, snow will fall.

name: Zapdos
info:
Zapdos is a legendary Electric & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice and Rock moves. Zapdos's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 3,527.
					
						"Zapdos is a Legendary Pokémon that has the ability to control electricity. It usually lives in thunderclouds. The Pokémon gains power if it is stricken by lightning bolts.

name: Moltres
info:
Moltres is a legendary Fire & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Electric and Water moves. Moltres's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 3,465.
					
						"Moltres is a Legendary Pokémon that has the ability to control fire. If this Pokémon is injured, it is said to dip its body in the molten magma of a volcano to burn and heal itself.

name: Dratini
info:
Dratini is a Dragon Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Dratini's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 1,004. Dratini evolves into Dragonair.
					
						"Dratini continually molts and sloughs off its old skin. It does so because the life energy within its body steadily builds to reach uncontrollable levels.

name: Dragonair
info:
Dragonair is a Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Dratini. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Dragon and Ice moves. Dragonair's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Dragon Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,780. Dragonair evolves into Dragonite.
					
						"Dragonair stores an enormous amount of energy inside its body. It is said to alter weather conditions in its vicinity by discharging energy from the crystals on its neck and tail.

name: Dragonite
info:
Dragonite is a Dragon & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Dragonair. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy, Dragon and Rock moves. Dragonite's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Outrage and it has a Max CP of 3,792.
					
						"Dragonite is capable of circling the globe in just 16 hours. It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.

name: Mewtwo
info:
Mewtwo (Armored) is a legendary Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Mewtwo's strongest moveset is Confusion & Future Sight and it has a Max CP of 3,187.
					
						"Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon's body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.

name: Mewtwo
info:
Mewtwo (Normal) is a legendary Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Mewtwo's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 4,178.
					
						"Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon's body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.

name: Mew
info:
Mew is a mythical Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Mew's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,265.
					
						"Mew is said to possess the genetic composition of all Pokémon. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.

name: Chikorita
info:
Chikorita is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Chikorita's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 935. Chikorita evolves into Bayleef.
					
						"In battle, Chikorita waves its leaf around to keep the foe at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, becalming the battling Pokémon and creating a cozy, friendly atmosphere all around.

name: Bayleef
info:
Bayleef is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Chikorita. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Bayleef's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,454. Bayleef evolves into Meganium.
					
						"Bayleef's neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each tubular leaf is a small shoot of a tree. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

name: Meganium
info:
Meganium is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Bayleef. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Meganium's strongest moveset is Vine Whip & Frenzy Plant and it has a Max CP of 2,410.
					
						"The fragrance of Meganium's flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe's fighting spirit.

name: Cyndaquil
info:
Cyndaquil is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Cyndaquil's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 980. Cyndaquil evolves into Quilava.
					
						"Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames splutter fitfully with incomplete combustion.

name: Quilava
info:
Quilava is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Cyndaquil. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Quilava's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,653. Quilava evolves into Typhlosion.
					
						"Quilava keeps its foes at bay with the intensity of its flames and gusts of superheated air. This Pokémon applies its outstanding nimbleness to dodge attacks even while scorching the foe with flames.

name: Typhlosion
info:
Typhlosion is a Fire Pokémon which evolves from Quilava. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Typhlosion's strongest moveset is Ember & Blast Burn and it has a Max CP of 2,889.
					
						"Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokémon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.

name: Totodile
info:
Totodile is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Totodile's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,131. Totodile evolves into Croconaw.
					
						"Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile's jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.

name: Croconaw
info:
Croconaw is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Totodile. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Croconaw's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 1,722. Croconaw evolves into Feraligatr.
					
						"Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.

name: Feraligatr
info:
Feraligatr is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Croconaw. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Feraligatr's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Hydro Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,857.
					
						"Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.

name: Sentret
info:
Sentret is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Sentret's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 618. Sentret evolves into Furret.
					
						"When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.

name: Furret
info:
Furret is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Sentret. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Furret's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,758.
					
						"Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.

name: Hoothoot
info:
Hoothoot is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Hoothoot's strongest moveset is Peck & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 677. Hoothoot evolves into Noctowl.
					
						"Hoothoot has an internal organ that senses and tracks the earth's rotation. Using this special organ, this Pokémon begins hooting at precisely the same time every day.

name: Noctowl
info:
Noctowl is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Hoothoot. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Noctowl's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 2,024.
					
						"Noctowl never fails at catching prey in darkness. This Pokémon owes its success to its superior vision that allows it to see in minimal light, and to its soft, supple wings that make no sound in flight.

name: Ledyba
info:
Ledyba is a Bug & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Ledyba's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 728. Ledyba evolves into Ledian.
					
						"Ledyba secretes an aromatic fluid from where its legs join its body. This fluid is used for communicating with others. This Pokémon conveys its feelings to others by altering the fluid's scent.

name: Ledian
info:
Ledian is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Ledyba. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Ledian's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,346.
					
						"It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live Ledian in countless numbers. There is a good reason for this—the Pokémon uses the light of the stars as its energy.

name: Spinarak
info:
Spinarak is a Bug & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Spinarak's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Signal Beam and it has a Max CP of 816. Spinarak evolves into Ariados.
					
						"The web spun by Spinarak can be considered its second nervous system. It is said that this Pokémon can determine what kind of prey is touching its web just by the tiny vibrations it feels through the web's strands.

name: Ariados
info:
Ariados is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Spinarak. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Ariados's strongest moveset is Infestation & Megahorn and it has a Max CP of 1,772.
					
						"Ariados's feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and vertical walls. This Pokémon constricts the foe with thin and strong silk webbing.

name: Crobat
info:
Crobat is a Poison & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Golbat. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock, Psychic and Electric moves. Crobat's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 2,646.
					
						"If this Pokémon is flying by fluttering only a pair of wings on either the forelegs or hind legs, it's proof that Crobat has been flying a long distance. It switches the wings it uses if it is tired.

name: Chinchou
info:
Chinchou is a Water & Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground and Grass moves. Chinchou's strongest moveset is Bubble & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,119. Chinchou evolves into Lanturn.
					
						"Chinchou lets loose positive and negative electrical charges from its two antennas to make its prey faint. This Pokémon flashes its electric lights to exchange signals with others.

name: Lanturn
info:
Lanturn is a Water & Electric Pokémon which evolves from Chinchou. It is vulnerable to Ground and Grass moves. Lanturn's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 2,085.
					
						"Lanturn is nicknamed “the deep-sea star” for its illuminated antenna. This Pokémon produces light by causing a chemical reaction between bacteria and its bodily fluids inside the antenna.

name: Pichu
info:
Pichu is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Pichu's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 473. Pichu evolves into Pikachu.
					
						"Pichu charges itself with electricity more easily on days with thunderclouds or when the air is very dry. You can hear the crackling of static electricity coming off this Pokémon.

name: Cleffa
info:
Cleffa is a Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Cleffa's strongest moveset is Pound & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 671. Cleffa evolves into Clefairy.
					
						"On nights with many shooting stars, Cleffa can be seen dancing in a ring. They dance through the night and stop only at the break of day, when these Pokémon quench their thirst with the morning dew.

name: Igglybuff
info:
Igglybuff is a Normal & Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Igglybuff's strongest moveset is Pound & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 535. Igglybuff evolves into Jigglypuff.
					
						"Igglybuff's vocal cords are not sufficiently developed. It would hurt its throat if it were to sing too much. This Pokémon gargles with freshwater from a clean stream.

name: Togepi
info:
Togepi is a Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Togepi's strongest moveset is Hidden Power & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 657. Togepi evolves into Togetic.
					
						"As its energy, Togepi uses the positive emotions of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and Pokémon. This Pokémon stores up feelings of happiness inside its shell, then shares them with others.
