name: Togetic
info:
Togetic is a Fairy & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Togepi. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ice, Poison, Rock and Electric moves. Togetic's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 1,708. Togetic evolves into Togekiss.
					
						"Togetic is said to be a Pokémon that brings good fortune. When the Pokémon spots someone who is pure of heart, it is said to appear and share its happiness with that person.

name: Natu
info:
Natu is a Psychic & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ice, Rock, Electric and Ghost moves. Natu's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Drill Peck and it has a Max CP of 1,102. Natu evolves into Xatu.
					
						"Natu cannot fly because its wings are not yet fully grown. If your eyes meet with this Pokémon's eyes, it will stare back intently at you. But if you move even slightly, it will hop away to safety.

name: Xatu
info:
Xatu is a Psychic & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Natu. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ice, Rock, Electric and Ghost moves. Xatu's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Future Sight and it has a Max CP of 2,188.
					
						"Xatu stands rooted and still in one spot all day long. People believe that this Pokémon does so out of fear of the terrible things it has foreseen in the future.

name: Mareep
info:
Mareep is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Mareep's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 991. Mareep evolves into Flaaffy.
					
						"Mareep's fluffy coat of wool rubs together and builds a static charge. The more static electricity is charged, the more brightly the lightbulb at the tip of its tail glows.

name: Flaaffy
info:
Flaaffy is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Mareep. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Flaaffy's strongest moveset is Charge Beam & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,521. Flaaffy evolves into Ampharos.
					
						"Flaaffy's wool quality changes so that it can generate a high amount of static electricity with a small amount of wool. The bare and slick parts of its hide are shielded against electricity.

name: Ampharos
info:
Ampharos is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Flaaffy. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Ampharos's strongest moveset is Charge Beam & Zap Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,852.
					
						"Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.

name: Bellossom
info:
Bellossom is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Gloom. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Bellossom's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Leaf Blade and it has a Max CP of 2,281.
					
						"When Bellossom gets exposed to plenty of sunlight, the leaves ringing its body begin to spin around. This Pokémon's dancing is renowned in the southern lands.

name: Marill
info:
Marill is a Water & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Azurill. It is vulnerable to Poison, Electric and Grass moves. Marill's strongest moveset is Bubble & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 461. Marill evolves into Azumarill.
					
						"Marill's oil-filled tail acts much like a life preserver. If you see just its tail bobbing on the water's surface, it's a sure indication that this Pokémon is diving beneath the water to feed on aquatic plants.

name: Azumarill
info:
Azumarill is a Water & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Marill. It is vulnerable to Poison, Electric and Grass moves. Azumarill's strongest moveset is Bubble & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,588.
					
						"Azumarill's long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its hearing, this Pokémon can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and fast-running rivers.

name: Sudowoodo
info:
Sudowoodo is a Rock Pokémon which evolves from Bonsly. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Sudowoodo's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 2,148.
					
						"Sudowoodo camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because its hands remain green throughout the year, the Pokémon is easily identified as a fake during the winter.

name: Politoed
info:
Politoed is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Poliwhirl. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Politoed's strongest moveset is Bubble & Surf and it has a Max CP of 2,449.
					
						"The curled hair on Politoed's head is proof of its status as a king. It is said that the longer and more curled the hair, the more respect this Pokémon earns from its peers.

name: Hoppip
info:
Hoppip is a Grass & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fire, Flying, Poison and Rock moves. Hoppip's strongest moveset is Bullet Seed & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 600. Hoppip evolves into Skiploom.
					
						"This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.

name: Skiploom
info:
Skiploom is a Grass & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Hoppip. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fire, Flying, Poison and Rock moves. Skiploom's strongest moveset is Bullet Seed & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 976. Skiploom evolves into Jumpluff.
					
						"Skiploom's flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.

name: Jumpluff
info:
Jumpluff is a Grass & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Skiploom. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fire, Flying, Poison and Rock moves. Jumpluff's strongest moveset is Infestation & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,636.
					
						"Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

name: Aipom
info:
Aipom is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Aipom's strongest moveset is Scratch & Swift and it has a Max CP of 1,348. Aipom evolves into Ambipom.
					
						"Aipom's tail ends in a hand-like appendage that can be cleverly manipulated. However, because the Pokémon uses its tail so much, its real hands have become rather clumsy.

name: Sunkern
info:
Sunkern is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Sunkern's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 395. Sunkern evolves into Sunflora.
					
						"Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.

name: Sunflora
info:
Sunflora is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Sunkern. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Sunflora's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,141.
					
						"Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.

name: Yanma
info:
Yanma is a Bug & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Yanma's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 1,470. Yanma evolves into Yanmega.
					
						"Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.

name: Wooper
info:
Wooper is a Water & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Wooper's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Mud Bomb and it has a Max CP of 641. Wooper evolves into Quagsire.
					
						"Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.

name: Quagsire
info:
Quagsire is a Water & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Wooper. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Quagsire's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 1,992.
					
						"Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon does not move, it does not get very hungry.

name: Espeon
info:
Espeon is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Espeon's strongest moveset is Confusion & Future Sight and it has a Max CP of 3,170.
					
						"Espeon is extremely loyal to any Trainer it considers to be worthy. It is said that this Pokémon developed its precognitive powers to protect its Trainer from harm.

name: Umbreon
info:
Umbreon is a Dark Pokémon which evolves from Eevee. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Umbreon's strongest moveset is Snarl & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 2,137.
					
						"Umbreon evolved as a result of exposure to the moon's waves. It hides silently in darkness and waits for its foes to make a move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.

name: Murkrow
info:
Murkrow is a Dark & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Ice, Electric and Rock moves. Murkrow's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 1,562. Murkrow evolves into Honchkrow.
					
						"Murkrow was feared and loathed as the alleged bearer of ill fortune. This Pokémon shows strong interest in anything that sparkles or glitters. It will even try to steal rings from women.

name: Slowking
info:
Slowking is a Water & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Slowpoke. It is vulnerable to Ghost, Dark, Electric, Grass and Bug moves. Slowking's strongest moveset is Confusion & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 2,545.
					
						"Slowking undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this Pokémon apparently forgets everything it has learned if the Shellder on its head comes off.

name: Misdreavus
info:
Misdreavus is a Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Misdreavus's strongest moveset is Hex & Ominous Wind and it has a Max CP of 1,926. Misdreavus evolves into Mismagius.
					
						"Misdreavus frightens people with a creepy, sobbing cry. The Pokémon apparently uses its red spheres to absorb the fearful feelings of foes and turn them into nutrition.

name: Unown
info:
Unown is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Unown's strongest moveset is Hidden Power & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 1,185.
					
						"This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

name: Wobbuffet
info:
Wobbuffet is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Wynaut. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Wobbuffet's strongest moveset is Counter & Mirror Coat and it has a Max CP of 1,026.
					
						"If two or more Wobbuffet meet, they will turn competitive and try to outdo each other's endurance. However, they may try to see which one can endure the longest without food. Trainers need to beware of this habit.

name: Girafarig
info:
Girafarig is a Normal & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug and Dark moves. Girafarig's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 2,046.
					
						"Girafarig's rear head also has a brain, but it is small. The rear head attacks in response to smells and sounds. Approaching this Pokémon from behind can cause the rear head to suddenly lash out and bite.

name: Pineco
info:
Pineco is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Pineco's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Gyro Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,108. Pineco evolves into Forretress.
					
						"Pineco hangs from a tree branch and patiently waits for prey to come along. If the Pokémon is disturbed while eating by someone shaking its tree, it drops down to the ground and explodes with no warning.

name: Forretress
info:
Forretress is a Bug & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Pineco. It is vulnerable to Fire moves. Forretress's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 2,282.
					
						"Forretress conceals itself inside its hardened steel shell. The shell is opened when the Pokémon is catching prey, but it does so at such a quick pace that the shell's inside cannot be seen.

name: Dunsparce
info:
Dunsparce is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Dunsparce's strongest moveset is Bite & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 1,689.
					
						"Dunsparce has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backward. This Pokémon is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.

name: Gligar
info:
Gligar is a Ground & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice and Water moves. Gligar's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,857. Gligar evolves into Gliscor.
					
						"Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.

name: Steelix
info:
Steelix is a Steel & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Onix. It is vulnerable to Fire, Water, Ground and Fighting moves. Steelix's strongest moveset is Iron Tail & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 2,414.
					
						"Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth's core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.

name: Snubbull
info:
Snubbull is a Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Snubbull's strongest moveset is Tackle & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 1,237. Snubbull evolves into Granbull.
					
						"By baring its fangs and making a scary face, Snubbull sends smaller Pokémon scurrying away in terror. However, this Pokémon seems a little sad at making its foes flee.

name: Granbull
info:
Granbull is a Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Snubbull. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Granbull's strongest moveset is Charm Fast & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 2,552.
					
						"Granbull has a particularly well-developed lower jaw. The enormous fangs are heavy, causing the Pokémon to tip its head back for balance. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite indiscriminately.

name: Qwilfish
info:
Qwilfish is a Water & Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Psychic and Electric moves. Qwilfish's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 2,051.
					
						"Qwilfish sucks in water, inflating itself. This Pokémon uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.

name: Scizor
info:
Scizor is a Bug & Steel Pokémon which evolves from Scyther. It is vulnerable to Fire moves. Scizor's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Iron Head and it has a Max CP of 3,001.
					
						"Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. This Pokémon flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.

name: Shuckle
info:
Shuckle is a Bug & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Rock and Steel moves. Shuckle's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 405.
					
						"Shuckle quietly hides itself under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its hard shell while eating berries it has stored away. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.

name: Heracross
info:
Heracross is a regional Bug & Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Flying, Fairy, Psychic and Fire moves. Heracross's strongest moveset is Counter & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 3,101. This Pokémon is only found in Latin America, south Florida, and Texas.
					
						"Heracross charges in a straight line at its foe, slips beneath the foe's grasp, and then scoops up and hurls the opponent with its mighty horn. This Pokémon even has enough power to topple a massive tree.

name: Sneasel
info:
Sneasel is a Dark & Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Fairy, Bug, Steel, Fire and Rock moves. Sneasel's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,051. Sneasel evolves into Weavile.
					
						"Sneasel scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. This Pokémon seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.

name: Teddiursa
info:
Teddiursa is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Teddiursa's strongest moveset is Scratch & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,328. Teddiursa evolves into Ursaring.
					
						"This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.

name: Ursaring
info:
Ursaring is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Teddiursa. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Ursaring's strongest moveset is Counter & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,945.
					
						"In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.

name: Slugma
info:
Slugma is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Slugma's strongest moveset is Ember & Flame Burst and it has a Max CP of 895. Slugma evolves into Magcargo.
					
						"Molten magma courses throughout Slugma's circulatory system. If this Pokémon is chilled, the magma cools and hardens. Its body turns brittle and chunks fall off, reducing its size.

name: Magcargo
info:
Magcargo is a Fire & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Slugma. It is vulnerable to Water, Ground, Rock and Fighting moves. Magcargo's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 1,702.
					
						"Magcargo's shell is actually its skin that hardened as a result of cooling. Its shell is very brittle and fragile—just touching it causes it to crumble apart. This Pokémon returns to its original size by dipping itself in magma.

name: Swinub
info:
Swinub is an Ice & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Grass, Water and Steel moves. Swinub's strongest moveset is Powder Snow & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 741. Swinub evolves into Piloswine.
					
						"Swinub roots for food by rubbing its snout against the ground. Its favorite food is a mushroom that grows under the cover of dead grass. This Pokémon occasionally roots out hot springs.

name: Piloswine
info:
Piloswine is an Ice & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Swinub. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Grass, Water and Steel moves. Piloswine's strongest moveset is Ice Shard & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,345. Piloswine evolves into Mamoswine.
					
						"Piloswine is covered by a thick coat of long hair that enables it to endure the freezing cold. This Pokémon uses its tusks to dig up food that has been buried under ice.

name: Corsola
info:
Corsola is a regional Water & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ground, Fighting and Electric moves. Corsola's strongest moveset is Bubble & Power Gem and it has a Max CP of 1,378. This Pokémon is only found in Tropics, near to the sea.
					
						"Corsola's branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night.

name: Remoraid
info:
Remoraid is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Remoraid's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Water Pulse and it has a Max CP of 912. Remoraid evolves into Octillery.
					
						"Remoraid sucks in water, then expels it at high velocity using its abdominal muscles to shoot down flying prey. When evolution draws near, this Pokémon travels downstream from rivers.

name: Octillery
info:
Octillery is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Remoraid. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Octillery's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 2,315.
					
						"Octillery grabs onto its foe using its tentacles. This Pokémon tries to immobilize it before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, Octillery spews ink to escape.

name: Delibird
info:
Delibird is an Ice & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Electric and Steel moves. Delibird's strongest moveset is Present & Ice Punch and it has a Max CP of 1,094.
					
						"Delibird carries its food bundled up in its tail. There once was a famous explorer who managed to reach the peak of the world's highest mountain, thanks to one of these Pokémon sharing its food.

name: Mantine
info:
Mantine is a Water & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Mantyke. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Mantine's strongest moveset is Bubble & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 2,108.
					
						"On sunny days, schools of Mantine can be seen elegantly leaping over the sea's waves. This Pokémon is not bothered by the Remoraid that hitches rides.

name: Skarmory
info:
Skarmory is a Steel & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire and Electric moves. Skarmory's strongest moveset is Steel Wing & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 2,108.
					
						"Skarmory is entirely encased in hard, protective armor. This Pokémon flies at close to 190 mph. It slashes foes with its wings that possess swordlike cutting edges.

name: Houndour
info:
Houndour is a Dark & Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Ground, Rock and Water moves. Houndour's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,234. Houndour evolves into Houndoom.
					
						"Houndour hunt as a coordinated pack. They communicate with each other using a variety of cries to corner their prey. This Pokémon's remarkable teamwork is unparalleled.

name: Houndoom
info:
Houndoom is a Dark & Fire Pokémon which evolves from Houndour. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Ground, Rock and Water moves. Houndoom's strongest moveset is Snarl & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 2,635.
					
						"In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokémon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

name: Kingdra
info:
Kingdra is a Water & Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Seadra. It is vulnerable to Fairy and Dragon moves. Kingdra's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Outrage and it has a Max CP of 2,641.
					
						"Kingdra lives at extreme ocean depths that are otherwise uninhabited. It has long been believed that the yawning of this Pokémon creates spiraling ocean currents.

name: Phanpy
info:
Phanpy is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Phanpy's strongest moveset is Tackle & Bulldoze and it has a Max CP of 1,206. Phanpy evolves into Donphan.
					
						"For its nest, Phanpy digs a vertical pit in the ground at the edge of a river. It marks the area around its nest with its trunk to let the others know that the area has been claimed.

name: Donphan
info:
Donphan is a Ground Pokémon which evolves from Phanpy. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Donphan's strongest moveset is Counter & Earthquake and it has a Max CP of 3,013.
					
						"Donphan's favorite attack is curling its body into a ball, then charging at its foe while rolling at high speed. Once it starts rolling, this Pokémon can't stop very easily.

name: Porygon2
info:
Porygon2 is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Porygon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Porygon2's strongest moveset is Hidden Power & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,711. Porygon2 evolves into Porygon-Z.
					
						"Porygon2 was created by humans using the power of science. The man-made Pokémon has been endowed with artificial intelligence that enables it to learn new gestures and emotions on its own.

name: Stantler
info:
Stantler is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Stantler's strongest moveset is Tackle & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 2,164.
					
						"Stantler's magnificent antlers were traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction by those who were after the priceless antlers.

name: Smeargle
info:
Smeargle is an unobtainable Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Smeargle's strongest moveset is Tackle & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 431.
					
						"Smeargle marks the boundaries of its territory using a body fluid that leaks out from the tip of its tail. Over 5,000 different marks left by this Pokémon have been found.

name: Tyrogue
info:
Tyrogue is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Tyrogue's strongest moveset is Rock Smash & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 492. Tyrogue evolves into Hitmonlee, Hitmonchan, Hitmontop.
					
						"Tyrogue becomes stressed out if it does not get to train every day. When raising this Pokémon, the Trainer must establish and uphold various training methods.

name: Hitmontop
info:
Hitmontop is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Tyrogue. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Hitmontop's strongest moveset is Counter & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,156.
					
						"Hitmontop spins on its head at high speed, all the while delivering kicks. This technique is a remarkable mix of both offense and defense at the same time. The Pokémon travels faster spinning than it does walking.

name: Smoochum
info:
Smoochum is an Ice & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Dark, Rock, Bug, Ghost and Steel moves. Smoochum's strongest moveset is Pound & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,291. Smoochum evolves into Jynx.
					
						"Smoochum actively runs about, but also falls quite often. Whenever the chance arrives, it will look for its reflection to make sure its face hasn't become dirty.

name: Elekid
info:
Elekid is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Elekid's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Discharge and it has a Max CP of 1,206. Elekid evolves into Electabuzz.
					
						"Elekid stores electricity in its body. If it touches metal and accidentally discharges all its built-up electricity, this Pokémon begins swinging its arms in circles to recharge itself.

name: Magby
info:
Magby is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Magby's strongest moveset is Ember & Fire Punch and it has a Max CP of 1,323. Magby evolves into Magmar.
					
						"Magby's state of health is determined by observing the fire it breathes. If the Pokémon is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.

name: Miltank
info:
Miltank is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Miltank's strongest moveset is Tackle & Body Slam and it has a Max CP of 2,354.
					
						"Miltank gives over five gallons of milk on a daily basis. Its sweet milk is enjoyed by children and grown-ups alike. People who can't drink milk turn it into yogurt and eat it instead.

name: Blissey
info:
Blissey is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Chansey. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Blissey's strongest moveset is Pound & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,757.
					
						"Blissey senses sadness with its fluffy coat of fur. If it does so, this Pokémon will rush over to a sad person, no matter how far away, to share a Lucky Egg that brings a smile to any face.

name: Raikou
info:
Raikou is a legendary Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Raikou's strongest moveset is Thunder Shock & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 3,452.
					
						"Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

name: Entei
info:
Entei is a legendary Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Entei's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 3,473.
					
						"Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

name: Suicune
info:
Suicune is a legendary Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Suicune's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,983.
					
						"Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

name: Larvitar
info:
Larvitar is a Rock & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Larvitar's strongest moveset is Bite & Ancient Power and it has a Max CP of 1,040. Larvitar evolves into Pupitar.
					
						"Larvitar is born deep under the ground. To come up to the surface, this Pokémon must eat its way through the soil above. Until it does so, Larvitar cannot see its parents.

name: Pupitar
info:
Pupitar is a Rock & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Larvitar. It is vulnerable to Water, Grass, Ground, Ice, Steel and Fighting moves. Pupitar's strongest moveset is Bite & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,766. Pupitar evolves into Tyranitar.
					
						"Pupitar creates a gas inside its body that it compresses and forcefully ejects to propel itself like a jet. The body is very durable—it avoids damage even if it hits solid steel.

name: Tyranitar
info:
Tyranitar is a Rock & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Pupitar. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Fairy, Ground, Bug, Steel, Water and Grass moves. Tyranitar's strongest moveset is Smack Down & Stone Edge and it has a Max CP of 3,834.
					
						"Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. This Pokémon wanders about in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.

name: Lugia
info:
Lugia is a legendary Psychic & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ice, Rock, Electric and Ghost moves. Lugia's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 3,703.
					
						"Lugia's wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

name: Ho
info:
Ho-Oh is a legendary Fire & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Electric and Water moves. Ho-Oh's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 3,863.
					
						"Ho-Oh's feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

name: Celebi
info:
Celebi is a mythical Psychic & Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fire, Ice, Flying, Poison, Dark and Ghost moves. Celebi's strongest moveset is Confusion & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 3,265.
					
						"This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

name: Treecko
info:
Treecko is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Treecko's strongest moveset is Pound & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,053. Treecko evolves into Grovyle.
					
						"Treecko has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This Pokémon attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

name: Grovyle
info:
Grovyle is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Treecko. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Grovyle's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,673. Grovyle evolves into Sceptile.
					
						"The leaves growing out of Grovyle's body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

name: Sceptile
info:
Sceptile is a Grass Pokémon which evolves from Grovyle. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Sceptile's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Frenzy Plant and it has a Max CP of 2,757.
					
						"The leaves growing on Sceptile's body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile—it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

name: Torchic
info:
Torchic is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Torchic's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,093. Torchic evolves into Combusken.
					
						"Torchic sticks with its Trainer, following behind with unsteady steps. This Pokémon breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.

name: Combusken
info:
Combusken is a Fire & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Torchic. It is vulnerable to Flying, Ground, Psychic and Water moves. Combusken's strongest moveset is Ember & Flamethrower and it has a Max CP of 1,652. Combusken evolves into Blaziken.
					
						"Combusken toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This Pokémon's legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out 10 kicks in one second.

name: Blaziken
info:
Blaziken is a Fire & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Combusken. It is vulnerable to Flying, Ground, Psychic and Water moves. Blaziken's strongest moveset is Counter & Blast Burn and it has a Max CP of 2,848.
					
						"In battle, Blaziken blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this Pokémon's wrists burn.

name: Mudkip
info:
Mudkip is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Mudkip's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Stomp and it has a Max CP of 1,128. Mudkip evolves into Marshtomp.
					
						"The fin on Mudkip's head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

name: Marshtomp
info:
Marshtomp is a Water & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Mudkip. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Marshtomp's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Surf and it has a Max CP of 1,776. Marshtomp evolves into Swampert.
					
						"The surface of Marshtomp's body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This Pokémon plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

name: Swampert
info:
Swampert is a Water & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Marshtomp. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Swampert's strongest moveset is Mud Shot & Hydro Cannon and it has a Max CP of 2,974.
					
						"Swampert is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This Pokémon also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.

name: Poochyena
info:
Poochyena is a Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Poochyena's strongest moveset is Snarl & Crunch and it has a Max CP of 678. Poochyena evolves into Mightyena.
					
						"At first sight, Poochyena takes a bite at anything that moves. This Pokémon chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.

name: Mightyena
info:
Mightyena is a Dark Pokémon which evolves from Poochyena. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Mightyena's strongest moveset is Bite & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,926.
					
						"Mightyena gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This Pokémon will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.

name: Zigzagoon
info:
Zigzagoon is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Zigzagoon's strongest moveset is Tackle & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 508. Zigzagoon evolves into Linoone.
					
						"Zigzagoon restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This Pokémon does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.

name: Linoone
info:
Linoone is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Zigzagoon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Linoone's strongest moveset is Tackle & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,662.
					
						"Linoone always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This Pokémon is very challenged by gently curving roads.

name: Wurmple
info:
Wurmple is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Wurmple's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 578. Wurmple evolves into Silcoon, Cascoon.
					
						"Using the spikes on its rear end, Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokémon's feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.

name: Silcoon
info:
Silcoon is a Bug Pokémon which evolves from Wurmple. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Silcoon's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 553. Silcoon evolves into Beautifly.
					
						"Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.

name: Beautifly
info:
Beautifly is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Silcoon. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Beautifly's strongest moveset is Infestation & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,765.
					
						"Beautifly's favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokémon, just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.

name: Cascoon
info:
Cascoon is a Bug Pokémon which evolves from Wurmple. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Cascoon's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Struggle and it has a Max CP of 553. Cascoon evolves into Dustox.
					
						"Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.

name: Dustox
info:
Dustox is a Bug & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Cascoon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Psychic moves. Dustox's strongest moveset is Confusion & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,224.
					
						"Dustox is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this Pokémon are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.

name: Lotad
info:
Lotad is a Water & Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Flying, Poison and Bug moves. Lotad's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Energy Ball and it has a Max CP of 598. Lotad evolves into Lombre.
					
						"Lotad live in ponds and lakes, where they float on the surface. It grows weak if its broad leaf dies. On rare occasions, this Pokémon travels on land in search of clean water.

name: Lombre
info:
Lombre is a Water & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Lotad. It is vulnerable to Flying, Poison and Bug moves. Lombre's strongest moveset is Bubble & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,197. Lombre evolves into Ludicolo.
					
						"Lombre is nocturnal—it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief maker. When this Pokémon spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.

name: Ludicolo
info:
Ludicolo is a Water & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Lombre. It is vulnerable to Flying, Poison and Bug moves. Ludicolo's strongest moveset is Bubble & Solar Beam and it has a Max CP of 2,323.
					
						"Ludicolo begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This Pokémon is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.

name: Seedot
info:
Seedot is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Seedot's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 598. Seedot evolves into Nuzleaf.
					
						"Seedot attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this Pokémon's body becomes.

name: Nuzleaf
info:
Nuzleaf is a Grass & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Seedot. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fairy, Ice, Fighting, Fire, Poison and Flying moves. Nuzleaf's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,227. Nuzleaf evolves into Shiftry.
					
						"Nuzleaf live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This Pokémon dislikes having its long nose pinched.

name: Shiftry
info:
Shiftry is a Grass & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Nuzleaf. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fairy, Ice, Fighting, Fire, Poison and Flying moves. Shiftry's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Leaf Blade and it has a Max CP of 2,333.
					
						"Shiftry is a mysterious Pokémon that is said to live atop towering trees dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.

name: Taillow
info:
Taillow is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Taillow's strongest moveset is Quick Attack & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 765. Taillow evolves into Swellow.
					
						"Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokémon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

name: Swellow
info:
Swellow is a Normal & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Taillow. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Swellow's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 1,920.
					
						"Swellow flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokémon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow's clawed feet, preventing escape.

name: Wingull
info:
Wingull is a Water & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Wingull's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 765. Wingull evolves into Pelipper.
					
						"Wingull has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This Pokémon rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.

name: Pelipper
info:
Pelipper is a Water & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Wingull. It is vulnerable to Electric and Rock moves. Pelipper's strongest moveset is Wing Attack & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,127.
					
						"Pelipper is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon and eggs inside its massive bill. This Pokémon builds its nest on steep cliffs facing the sea.

name: Ralts
info:
Ralts is a Psychic & Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Poison, Ghost and Steel moves. Ralts's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psyshock and it has a Max CP of 539. Ralts evolves into Kirlia.
					
						"Ralts senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This Pokémon rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.

name: Kirlia
info:
Kirlia is a Psychic & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Ralts. It is vulnerable to Poison, Ghost and Steel moves. Kirlia's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psychic and it has a Max CP of 966. Kirlia evolves into Gardevoir, Gallade.
					
						"It is said that a Kirlia that is exposed to the positive emotions of its Trainer grows beautiful. This Pokémon controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.

name: Gardevoir
info:
Gardevoir is a Psychic & Fairy Pokémon which evolves from Kirlia. It is vulnerable to Poison, Ghost and Steel moves. Gardevoir's strongest moveset is Confusion & Dazzling Gleam and it has a Max CP of 3,093.
					
						"Gardevoir has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its Trainer, this Pokémon is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.

name: Surskit
info:
Surskit is a Bug & Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Flying, Rock and Electric moves. Surskit's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Signal Beam and it has a Max CP of 791. Surskit evolves into Masquerain.
					
						"From the tips of its feet, Surskit secretes an oil that enables it to walk on water as if it were skating. This Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms in ponds and lakes.

name: Masquerain
info:
Masquerain is a Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Surskit. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Masquerain's strongest moveset is Air Slash & Silver Wind and it has a Max CP of 2,270.
					
						"Masquerain intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns on its antennas. This Pokémon flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction—even sideways and backwards—as if it were a helicopter.

name: Shroomish
info:
Shroomish is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Shroomish's strongest moveset is Bullet Seed & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 810. Shroomish evolves into Breloom.
					
						"Shroomish live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This Pokémon feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.

name: Breloom
info:
Breloom is a Grass & Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Shroomish. It is vulnerable to Flying, Fairy, Psychic, Ice, Fire and Poison moves. Breloom's strongest moveset is Counter & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 2,628.
					
						"Breloom closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This Pokémon's fighting technique puts boxers to shame.

name: Slakoth
info:
Slakoth is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Slakoth's strongest moveset is Yawn & Body Slam and it has a Max CP of 1,002. Slakoth evolves into Vigoroth.
					
						"Slakoth lolls around for over 20 hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This Pokémon's sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.

name: Vigoroth
info:
Vigoroth is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Slakoth. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Vigoroth's strongest moveset is Scratch & Body Slam and it has a Max CP of 1,968. Vigoroth evolves into Slaking.
					
						"Vigoroth is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply can't tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This Pokémon's stress level rises if it can't be moving constantly.

name: Slaking
info:
Slaking is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Vigoroth. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Slaking's strongest moveset is Yawn & Hyper Beam and it has a Max CP of 4,431.
					
						"Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this Pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.

name: Nincada
info:
Nincada is an unobtainable Bug & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Water, Flying and Ice moves. Nincada's strongest moveset is Bug Bite & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 768. Nincada evolves into Ninjask, Shedinja.
					
						"Nincada lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This Pokémon absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.

name: Ninjask
info:
Ninjask is an unobtainable Bug & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Nincada. It is vulnerable to Rock, Fire, Flying, Ice and Electric moves. Ninjask's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,969.
					
						"Ninjask moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this Pokémon was long believed to be invisible.

name: Shedinja
info:
Shedinja is an unobtainable Bug & Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Nincada. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Dark, Rock and Ghost moves. Shedinja's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 393.
					
						"Shedinja's hard body doesn't move—not even a twitch. In fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this Pokémon will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.

name: Whismur
info:
Whismur is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Whismur's strongest moveset is Pound & Stomp and it has a Max CP of 671. Whismur evolves into Loudred.
					
						"Normally, Whismur's voice is very quiet—it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this Pokémon senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.

name: Loudred
info:
Loudred is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Whismur. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Loudred's strongest moveset is Bite & Stomp and it has a Max CP of 1,327. Loudred evolves into Exploud.
					
						"Loudred's bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. It uses its voice to punish its foes. This Pokémon's round ears serve as loudspeakers.

name: Exploud
info:
Exploud is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Loudred. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Exploud's strongest moveset is Bite & Fire Blast and it has a Max CP of 2,347.
					
						"Exploud triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. If this Pokémon violently inhales from the ports on its body, it's a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.

name: Makuhita
info:
Makuhita is a Fighting Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Makuhita's strongest moveset is Rock Smash & Cross Chop and it has a Max CP of 817. Makuhita evolves into Hariyama.
					
						"Makuhita is tenacious—it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this Pokémon stores more energy in its body for evolving.

name: Hariyama
info:
Hariyama is a Fighting Pokémon which evolves from Makuhita. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Psychic moves. Hariyama's strongest moveset is Counter & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 2,829.
					
						"Hariyama practices its straight-arm slaps in any number of locations. One hit of this Pokémon's powerful, openhanded, straight-arm punches could snap a telephone pole in two.

name: Azurill
info:
Azurill is a Normal & Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel and Poison moves. Azurill's strongest moveset is Bubble & Body Slam and it has a Max CP of 364. Azurill evolves into Marill.
					
						"Azurill spins its tail as if it were a lasso, then hurls it far. The momentum of the throw sends its body flying, too. Using this unique action, one of these Pokémon managed to hurl itself a record 33 feet.

name: Nosepass
info:
Nosepass is a Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Steel, Ground, Fighting, Water and Grass moves. Nosepass's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 993. Nosepass evolves into Probopass.
					
						"Nosepass's magnetic nose is always pointed to the north. If two of these Pokémon meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they are close because their magnetic noses repel one another.

name: Skitty
info:
Skitty is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Skitty's strongest moveset is Tackle & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 739. Skitty evolves into Delcatty.
					
						"Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.

name: Delcatty
info:
Delcatty is a Normal Pokémon which evolves from Skitty. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Delcatty's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 1,496.
					
						"Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.

name: Sableye
info:
Sableye is a Dark & Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy moves. Sableye's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 1,476.
					
						"Sableye lead quiet lives deep inside caverns. They are feared, however, because these Pokémon are thought to steal the spirits of people when their eyes burn with a sinister glow in the darkness.

name: Mawile
info:
Mawile is a Steel & Fairy Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire and Ground moves. Mawile's strongest moveset is Bite & Play Rough and it has a Max CP of 1,634.
					
						"Mawile's huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, Mawile chomps it with its gaping jaws.

name: Aron
info:
Aron is a Steel & Rock Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting and Water moves. Aron's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Iron Head and it has a Max CP of 1,307. Aron evolves into Lairon.
					
						"This Pokémon has a body of steel. To make its body, Aron feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.

name: Lairon
info:
Lairon is a Steel & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Aron. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting and Water moves. Lairon's strongest moveset is Metal Claw & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 2,056. Lairon evolves into Aggron.
					
						"Lairon tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This Pokémon makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.

name: Aggron
info:
Aggron is a Steel & Rock Pokémon which evolves from Lairon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Fighting and Water moves. Aggron's strongest moveset is Iron Tail & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 3,000.
					
						"Aggron claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This Pokémon vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.

name: Meditite
info:
Meditite is a Fighting & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Ghost moves. Meditite's strongest moveset is Confusion & Psyshock and it has a Max CP of 693. Meditite evolves into Medicham.
					
						"Meditite undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this Pokémon always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.

name: Medicham
info:
Medicham is a Fighting & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Meditite. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Flying and Ghost moves. Medicham's strongest moveset is Counter & Dynamic Punch and it has a Max CP of 1,431.
					
						"It is said that through meditation, Medicham heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This Pokémon hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.

name: Electrike
info:
Electrike is an Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Electrike's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 965. Electrike evolves into Manectric.
					
						"Electrike stores electricity in its long body hair. This Pokémon stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.

name: Manectric
info:
Manectric is an Electric Pokémon which evolves from Electrike. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Manectric's strongest moveset is Charge Beam & Wild Charge and it has a Max CP of 2,340.
					
						"Manectric is constantly discharging electricity from its mane. The sparks sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this Pokémon creates thunderclouds.

name: Plusle
info:
Plusle is a regional Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Plusle's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,778. This Pokémon is only found in North America, South America, Africa.
					
						"Plusle always acts as a cheerleader for its partners. Whenever a teammate puts out a good effort in battle, this Pokémon shorts out its body to create the crackling noises of sparks to show its joy.

name: Minun
info:
Minun is a regional Electric Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground moves. Minun's strongest moveset is Spark & Thunderbolt and it has a Max CP of 1,694. This Pokémon is only found in Europe, Asia, Australasia.
					
						"Minun is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.

name: Volbeat
info:
Volbeat is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Volbeat's strongest moveset is Struggle Bug & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,771.
					
						"With the arrival of night, Volbeat emits light from its tail. It communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. This Pokémon is attracted by the sweet aroma of Illumise.

name: Illumise
info:
Illumise is a Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying and Rock moves. Illumise's strongest moveset is Struggle Bug & Bug Buzz and it has a Max CP of 1,771.
					
						"Illumise attracts a swarm of Volbeat using a sweet fragrance. Once the Volbeat have gathered, this Pokémon leads the lit-up swarm in drawing geometric designs on the canvas of the night sky.

name: Roselia
info:
Roselia is a Grass & Poison Pokémon which evolves from Budew. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Ice and Psychic moves. Roselia's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,870. Roselia evolves into Roserade.
					
						"Roselia shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this Pokémon brings serenity to living things.

name: Gulpin
info:
Gulpin is a Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Gulpin's strongest moveset is Pound & Gunk Shot and it has a Max CP of 866. Gulpin evolves into Swalot.
					
						"Virtually all of Gulpin's body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This Pokémon's stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.

name: Swalot
info:
Swalot is a Poison Pokémon which evolves from Gulpin. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Swalot's strongest moveset is Infestation & Sludge Bomb and it has a Max CP of 1,978.
					
						"When Swalot spots prey, it spurts out a hideously toxic fluid from its pores and sprays the target. Once the prey has weakened, this Pokémon gulps it down whole with its cavernous mouth.

name: Carvanha
info:
Carvanha is a Water & Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Bug, Electric, Grass and Fighting moves. Carvanha's strongest moveset is Snarl & Crunch and it has a Max CP of 1,020. Carvanha evolves into Sharpedo.
					
						"Carvanha's strongly developed jaws and its sharply pointed fangs pack the destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and sunk by this Pokémon.

name: Sharpedo
info:
Sharpedo is a Water & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Carvanha. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Bug, Electric, Grass and Fighting moves. Sharpedo's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Hydro Pump and it has a Max CP of 2,181.
					
						"Nicknamed “the bully of the sea,” Sharpedo is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these Pokémon can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.

name: Wailmer
info:
Wailmer is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Wailmer's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Heavy Slam and it has a Max CP of 1,468. Wailmer evolves into Wailord.
					
						"Wailmer's nostrils are located above its eyes. This playful Pokémon loves to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body out of its nostrils.

name: Wailord
info:
Wailord is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Wailmer. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Wailord's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Surf and it has a Max CP of 2,280.
					
						"Wailord is the largest of all identified Pokémon up to now. This giant Pokémon swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.

name: Numel
info:
Numel is a Fire & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water and Ground moves. Numel's strongest moveset is Ember & Bulldoze and it has a Max CP of 1,057. Numel evolves into Camerupt.
					
						"Numel is extremely dull witted—it doesn't notice being hit. However, it can't stand hunger for even a second. This Pokémon's body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

name: Camerupt
info:
Camerupt is a Fire & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Numel. It is vulnerable to Water and Ground moves. Camerupt's strongest moveset is Ember & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 2,193.
					
						"Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokémon's back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

name: Torkoal
info:
Torkoal is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Torkoal's strongest moveset is Fire Spin & Overheat and it has a Max CP of 2,093.
					
						"Torkoal digs through mountains in search of coal. If it finds some, it fills hollow spaces on its shell with the coal and burns it. If it is attacked, this Pokémon spouts thick black smoke to beat a retreat.

name: Spoink
info:
Spoink is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Spoink's strongest moveset is Zen Headbutt & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,334. Spoink evolves into Grumpig.
					
						"Spoink bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. As a result, this Pokémon cannot afford to stop bouncing—if it stops, its heart will stop.

name: Grumpig
info:
Grumpig is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Spoink. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Grumpig's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,369.
					
						"Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. When this Pokémon uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.

name: Spinda
info:
Spinda is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Spinda's strongest moveset is Sucker Punch & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,220.
					
						"All the Spinda that exist in the world are said to have utterly unique spot patterns. The shaky, tottering steps of this Pokémon give it the appearance of dancing.

name: Trapinch
info:
Trapinch is a Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass, Ice and Water moves. Trapinch's strongest moveset is Mud Shot & Dig and it has a Max CP of 1,274. Trapinch evolves into Vibrava.
					
						"Trapinch's nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit dug in sand. This Pokémon patiently waits for prey to tumble down the pit. Its giant jaws have enough strength to crush even boulders.

name: Vibrava
info:
Vibrava is a Ground & Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Trapinch. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy and Dragon moves. Vibrava's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Bulldoze and it has a Max CP of 1,225. Vibrava evolves into Flygon.
					
						"To make prey faint, Vibrava generates ultrasonic waves by vigorously making its two wings vibrate. This Pokémon's ultrasonic waves are so powerful, they can bring on headaches in people.

name: Flygon
info:
Flygon is a Ground & Dragon Pokémon which evolves from Vibrava. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy and Dragon moves. Flygon's strongest moveset is Dragon Tail & Dragon Claw and it has a Max CP of 2,661.
					
						"Flygon is nicknamed “the elemental spirit of the desert.” Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this Pokémon is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.

name: Cacnea
info:
Cacnea is a Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Poison, Bug and Ice moves. Cacnea's strongest moveset is Sucker Punch & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,242. Cacnea evolves into Cacturne.
					
						"Cacnea lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this Pokémon shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.

name: Cacturne
info:
Cacturne is a Grass & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Cacnea. It is vulnerable to Bug, Fairy, Ice, Fighting, Fire, Poison and Flying moves. Cacturne's strongest moveset is Sucker Punch & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 2,298.
					
						"During the daytime, Cacturne remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This Pokémon becomes active at night when the temperature drops.

name: Swablu
info:
Swablu is a Normal & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Rock and Electric moves. Swablu's strongest moveset is Peck & Aerial Ace and it has a Max CP of 824. Swablu evolves into Altaria.
					
						"Swablu has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. This Pokémon is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.

name: Altaria
info:
Altaria is a Dragon & Flying Pokémon which evolves from Swablu. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fairy, Dragon and Rock moves. Altaria's strongest moveset is Dragon Breath & Sky Attack and it has a Max CP of 2,004.
					
						"Altaria dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this Pokémon makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.

name: Zangoose
info:
Zangoose is a regional Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Zangoose's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Close Combat and it has a Max CP of 2,418. This Pokémon is only found in Europe, Asia, Australasia.
					
						"Memories of battling its archrival Seviper are etched into every cell of Zangoose's body. This Pokémon adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.

name: Seviper
info:
Seviper is a regional Poison Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Psychic and Ground moves. Seviper's strongest moveset is Poison Jab & Crunch and it has a Max CP of 2,105. This Pokémon is only found in North America, South America, Africa.
					
						"Seviper shares a generations-long feud with Zangoose. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This Pokémon attacks using its sword-edged tail.

name: Lunatone
info:
Lunatone is a Rock & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Bug, Ghost, Steel, Water and Grass moves. Lunatone's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 2,327.
					
						"Lunatone was discovered at a location where a meteoroid fell. As a result, some people theorize that this Pokémon came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.

name: Solrock
info:
Solrock is a Rock & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark, Ground, Bug, Ghost, Steel, Water and Grass moves. Solrock's strongest moveset is Rock Throw & Rock Slide and it has a Max CP of 2,327.
					
						"Solrock is a new species of Pokémon that is said to have fallen from space. It floats in air and moves silently. In battle, this Pokémon releases intensely bright light.

name: Barboach
info:
Barboach is a Water & Ground Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Barboach's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 819. Barboach evolves into Whiscash.
					
						"Barboach's sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. This Pokémon hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.

name: Whiscash
info:
Whiscash is a Water & Ground Pokémon which evolves from Barboach. It is vulnerable to Grass moves. Whiscash's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Mud Bomb and it has a Max CP of 2,075.
					
						"Whiscash is extremely territorial. Just one of these Pokémon will claim a large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes about and triggers a massive earthquake.

name: Corphish
info:
Corphish is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Corphish's strongest moveset is Bubble & Bubble Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,230. Corphish evolves into Crawdaunt.
					
						"Corphish were originally foreign Pokémon that were imported as pets. They eventually turned up in the wild. This Pokémon is very hardy and has greatly increased its population.

name: Crawdaunt
info:
Crawdaunt is a Water & Dark Pokémon which evolves from Corphish. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Bug, Electric, Grass and Fighting moves. Crawdaunt's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Night Slash and it has a Max CP of 2,474.
					
						"Crawdaunt has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this Pokémon, making them desolate places.

name: Baltoy
info:
Baltoy is a Ground & Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Dark, Ice, Grass, Bug and Ghost moves. Baltoy's strongest moveset is Confusion & Dig and it has a Max CP of 787. Baltoy evolves into Claydol.
					
						"Baltoy moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this Pokémon living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.

name: Claydol
info:
Claydol is a Ground & Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Baltoy. It is vulnerable to Water, Dark, Ice, Grass, Bug and Ghost moves. Claydol's strongest moveset is Confusion & Earth Power and it has a Max CP of 1,971.
					
						"Claydol are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This Pokémon moves about while levitating.

name: Lileep
info:
Lileep is a Rock & Grass Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Ice, Bug and Steel moves. Lileep's strongest moveset is Infestation & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 1,291. Lileep evolves into Cradily.
					
						"Lileep became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient Pokémon attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles shaped like flower petals.

name: Cradily
info:
Cradily is a Rock & Grass Pokémon which evolves from Lileep. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Ice, Bug and Steel moves. Cradily's strongest moveset is Infestation & Grass Knot and it has a Max CP of 2,211.
					
						"Cradily roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This Pokémon freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.

name: Anorith
info:
Anorith is a Rock & Bug Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Water, Rock and Steel moves. Anorith's strongest moveset is Struggle Bug & Ancient Power and it has a Max CP of 1,529. Anorith evolves into Armaldo.
					
						"Anorith was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive Pokémon once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.

name: Armaldo
info:
Armaldo is a Rock & Bug Pokémon which evolves from Anorith. It is vulnerable to Water, Rock and Steel moves. Armaldo's strongest moveset is Fury Cutter & Rock Blast and it has a Max CP of 2,848.
					
						"Armaldo's tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This Pokémon's two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.

name: Feebas
info:
Feebas is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Feebas's strongest moveset is Tackle & Mirror Coat and it has a Max CP of 274. Feebas evolves into Milotic.
					
						"Feebas's fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this Pokémon is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.

name: Milotic
info:
Milotic is a Water Pokémon which evolves from Feebas. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Milotic's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Surf and it has a Max CP of 3,005.
					
						"Milotic is said to be the most beautiful of all the Pokémon. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.

name: Castform
info:
Castform (Rainy) is a Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Castform's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Weather Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,632.
					
						"Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

name: Castform
info:
Castform (Normal) is a Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Castform's strongest moveset is Tackle & Weather Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,632.
					
						"Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

name: Castform
info:
Castform (Snowy) is an Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Castform's strongest moveset is Powder Snow & Weather Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,632.
					
						"Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

name: Castform
info:
Castform (Sunny) is a Fire Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ground, Rock and Water moves. Castform's strongest moveset is Ember & Weather Ball and it has a Max CP of 1,632.
					
						"Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

name: Kecleon
info:
Kecleon is an unobtainable Normal Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting moves. Kecleon's strongest moveset is Lick & Foul Play and it has a Max CP of 2,047.
					
						"Kecleon is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception—this Pokémon can't change the zigzag pattern on its belly.

name: Shuppet
info:
Shuppet is a Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Shuppet's strongest moveset is Feint Attack & Ominous Wind and it has a Max CP of 1,018. Shuppet evolves into Banette.
					
						"Shuppet is attracted by feelings of jealousy and vindictiveness. If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this Pokémon will appear in a swarm and line up beneath the eaves of that person's home.

name: Banette
info:
Banette is a Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Shuppet. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Banette's strongest moveset is Shadow Claw & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,298.
					
						"Banette generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This Pokémon was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.

name: Duskull
info:
Duskull is a Ghost Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Duskull's strongest moveset is Hex & Ominous Wind and it has a Max CP of 706. Duskull evolves into Dusclops.
					
						"Duskull can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this Pokémon chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.

name: Dusclops
info:
Dusclops is a Ghost Pokémon which evolves from Duskull. It is vulnerable to Dark and Ghost moves. Dusclops's strongest moveset is Hex & Shadow Punch and it has a Max CP of 1,591. Dusclops evolves into Dusknoir.
					
						"Dusclops's body is completely hollow—there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This Pokémon will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.

name: Tropius
info:
Tropius is a Grass & Flying Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Ice, Fire, Flying, Poison and Rock moves. Tropius's strongest moveset is Razor Leaf & Leaf Blade and it has a Max CP of 1,941.
					
						"The bunches of fruit around Tropius's neck are very popular with children. This Pokémon loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.

name: Chimecho
info:
Chimecho is a Psychic Pokémon which evolves from Chingling. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Chimecho's strongest moveset is Extrasensory & Shadow Ball and it has a Max CP of 2,259.
					
						"Chimecho makes its cries echo inside its hollow body. When this Pokémon becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have the power to knock foes flying.

name: Absol
info:
Absol is a Dark Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fairy, Fighting and Bug moves. Absol's strongest moveset is Snarl & Dark Pulse and it has a Max CP of 2,526.
					
						"Every time Absol appears before people, it is followed by a disaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the disaster Pokémon.

name: Wynaut
info:
Wynaut is a Psychic Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Bug, Dark and Ghost moves. Wynaut's strongest moveset is Counter & Mirror Coat and it has a Max CP of 534. Wynaut evolves into Wobbuffet.
					
						"Wynaut can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this Pokémon will be slapping the ground with its tail.

name: Snorunt
info:
Snorunt is an Ice Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Snorunt's strongest moveset is Powder Snow & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 888. Snorunt evolves into Glalie, Froslass.
					
						"Snorunt live in regions with heavy snowfall. In seasons without snow, such as spring and summer, this Pokémon steals away to live quietly among stalactites and stalagmites deep in caverns.

name: Glalie
info:
Glalie is an Ice Pokémon which evolves from Snorunt. It is vulnerable to Fire, Fighting, Rock and Steel moves. Glalie's strongest moveset is Frost Breath & Avalanche and it has a Max CP of 2,105.
					
						"Glalie has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This Pokémon has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.

name: Spheal
info:
Spheal is an Ice & Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Spheal's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aurora Beam and it has a Max CP of 962. Spheal evolves into Sealeo.
					
						"Spheal is much faster rolling than walking to get around. When groups of this Pokémon eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.

name: Sealeo
info:
Sealeo is an Ice & Water Pokémon which evolves from Spheal. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Sealeo's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aurora Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,714. Sealeo evolves into Walrein.
					
						"Sealeo has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This Pokémon occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a Spheal on its nose.

name: Walrein
info:
Walrein is an Ice & Water Pokémon which evolves from Sealeo. It is vulnerable to Fighting, Rock, Electric and Grass moves. Walrein's strongest moveset is Waterfall & Blizzard and it has a Max CP of 2,726.
					
						"Walrein's two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing 10 tons with one blow. This Pokémon's thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.

name: Clamperl
info:
Clamperl is an unobtainable Water Pokémon. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Clamperl's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Ice Beam and it has a Max CP of 1,270. Clamperl evolves into Huntail, Gorebyss.
					
						"Clamperl's sturdy shell is not only good for protection—it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown Clamperl's shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.

name: Huntail
info:
Huntail is an unobtainable Water Pokémon which evolves from Clamperl. It is vulnerable to Grass and Electric moves. Huntail's strongest moveset is Water Gun & Aqua Tail and it has a Max CP of 2,340.
